Package: aviculture
Type: Package
Title: Broiler Growth Model and Interpolation for Ross 308 Chickens
Version: 0.2.0
Author: person("Aviculture", "Team", email = "contact@aviculture.dev", 
               role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Aviculture Team <contact@aviculture.dev>
Description: A comprehensive R package for modeling and predicting broiler chicken
    growth dynamics. It implements multi-tissue density modeling and multiple
    interpolation methods (Spline, Lagrange, Gompertz, Radial Basis Functions)
    to accurately predict mass and volume growth from 1 to 60 days of age.
    Based on Ross 308 broiler genetic line data, the package provides functions
    for trajectory simulation, growth rate calculation, tissue composition analysis,
    and validation against observed data. The mathematical framework accounts for
    biological changes in tissue composition during growth, ensuring physically
    realistic predictions with minimal overfitting.
    Includes numerical methods (explicit Euler ODE solver, trapezoidal integration,
    derivative approximations) for accurate simulation and API support via Plumber.
